item.title: Power BI Developer for Amazon Search Query Dashboard - Upwork
item.description:
We are seeking an experienced Power BI developer to create an Amazon Search Query Dashboard. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in data visualization and analytics, particularly with Power BI, and will be able to turn raw data into actionable insights.

Responsibilities:
- Develop a comprehensive Power BI dashboard to visualize Amazon search query data.
- Integrate various data sources, including Amazon APIs, to ensure real-time updates.
- Create dynamic and interactive visualizations, including charts, graphs, and tables, to represent search query performance metrics.
- Implement filtering and drill-down features to enhance data exploration and user interaction.
- Ensure the dashboard is user-friendly and accessible to non-technical stakeholders.
- Collaborate with our team to define key performance indicators (KPIs) and metrics for tracking search query performance.
- Provide documentation and training on dashboard use and maintenance.

Requirements:
- Proven experience with Power BI development and data visualization.
- Strong understanding of data modeling, DAX, and Power Query.
- Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills.
- Attention to detail and a commitment to delivering high-quality work.
- Good communication skills and the ability to work collaboratively.

Preferred Qualifications:
- Experience with Amazon search query data or e-commerce analytics.
- Familiarity with other BI tools and data analytics platforms.
- Knowledge of database management and SQL.

How to Apply:
Please submit your resume, a brief cover letter, and examples of previous Power BI dashboards you have developed.

Budget: $10

item.title: Microsoft Dataverse & Power BI Expert - Manufacturing Process Analytics - Upwork
item.description:
We are a manufacturing processing company with multiple locations, products, vendors, and customers. We currently manage our processing data in a SQL Server database and utilize various Excel reports and charts.
We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Microsoft Dataverse and Power BI developer to build a modern data analytics platform to streamline our reporting and gain deeper insights.
Key Responsibilities:
• Design and implement a Microsoft Dataverse environment for ingesting and managing our processing data.
• Develop robust Power BI reports and dashboards to visualize key performance indicators (KPIs) across locations, products, vendors, and customers.
• Establish data relationships and build interactive maps (optional, but highly desirable).
• Integrate with our existing on-premise SQL Server database for seamless data flow.
• Configure automated data refresh for daily updates and ideally achieve near real-time data reporting.
• Provide weekly progress reports and collaborate closely with our team members.
Desired Skills and Experience:
• Proven experience in Microsoft Dataverse design and implementation.
• Expertise in building compelling and interactive Power BI reports and dashboards.
• In-depth knowledge of data modeling and DAX scripting.
• Experience working with SQL Server and integrating with Power BI.
• Familiarity with manufacturing data and processes (a plus).
• Excellent communication and collaboration skills.
Budget:
We are open to competitive rates and are seeking a freelancer who can deliver high-quality work within a reasonable budget.
Project Timeline:
This project is expected to be completed within approximately 2 months.
Future Considerations:
We envision expanding our data analytics platform to include financial data from our Dynamics ERP system and potentially integrate forecasting components.
Please Note:
While location is not a primary factor, fluency in English and strong communication skills are essential. Please provide 2-3 examples including visuals of previous projects you’ve completed and include data structuring, PowerBI dashboards, and note any challenges you had to overcome.
We look forward to hearing from talented Power BI and Dataverse developers who are passionate about creating impactful data solutions.



Posted On: July 06, 2024 15:44 UTC
Category: Data Analytics
Skills:Business Intelligence, Data Visualization, Microsoft Power BI Development, Microsoft Azure SQL Database
Skills: Business Intelligence, Data Visualization, Microsoft Power BI Development, Microsoft Azure SQL Database
Country: United States

item.title: SPSS Modeler Expert Needed for Data Analysis and Report Writing - Upwork
item.description:
We are seeking an expert in SPSS Modeler to analyze a dataset and write a comprehensive report of approximately 3000 words. The ideal candidate should have a strong background in statistical analysis, data mining, and report writing. This project requires a deep understanding of SPSS Modeler and its various functionalities. The chosen freelancer will be responsible for performing an in-depth analysis of the dataset, identifying patterns and trends, and presenting the findings in a clear and concise manner. Excellent communication and problem-solving skills are essential to effectively communicate the results.

The project will take an expert under a week to complete. Short report no more than 3000 The word limit is 3000 words, however lot of this (approximately half) will consist of tables and appendices reporting results arising from the analysis.
The dataset contains data from different cars from different brands with a lot of data points. I will provide access to this dataset.

The report must include a brief introduction(What is the problem?
● Who are the stakeholders?
● Why does this problem matter to each stakeholder?

Data Set and Visualization
● Type of the dataset
● Dimensions of the dataset
● Variables, definitions, their types, and their roles
● Verbal presentation of at least two records
● Level of the data, what is each record about?
● Uni-variate visualization and commenting
o The measures of centrality and spread should be pointed to
● Bi-variate visualization and commenting (target vs predictor)
o Especially comment on the predictive power of the features
● Data Quality Assessment and treatment
o Outliers and extremes (definition and treatment)
o Missing values (definition and treatment)

Model and Results
● Predictive modelling formulation (what you want to predict and how)
● Type of the problem (classification? Regression?)
● Do we need data partitioning? Why?
● Underlining the performance metrics that you can use, and your metric choice
for this problem (the definition of the metric, and the rationale behind picking
it)
● Base-line model set-up and getting its performance on the testing set
● Feature engineering efforts
● Efforts to improve the model’s performance as summary table of the models
you have used,
● hyper-parameters of those models, any change in the features, and the
performance on the
● training and on the testing set
● A very brief introduction of every supervised/unsupervised method that has
been used
● Error cost analysis from the point of view of stakeholder(s). Which error is the
worst and
● why?

The end result: I need a report and the SPSS files to confirm what was used


Budget: $1,500

The immediate business needs we have:
- To improve product recommendations using TigerGraph (or similar tools/options) and our surrounding EcoSystem.

- Work with key stakeholders that are non-technical and be able to break complex problems to easy-to-understand speak

If interested in what this opportunity could look like moving to full-time, the below is a more complete job spec:

Responsibilities:
- Design and develop machine learning algorithms, deep learning applications, and systems.
- Construct optimized data pipelines to feed machine learning models.
- Collaborate with product teams to define and refine machine learning projects that align with business goals.
- Develop and maintain scalable and robust machine learning models to drive user engagement and satisfaction.
- Utilize a variety of datasets to train and validate models, ensuring accuracy and efficiency in real-world applications.
Implement advanced machine learning techniques, including supervised and unsupervised learning, deep learning, and anomaly detection.
- Optimize and troubleshoot the current recommendation system built on a graph database, ensuring it operates effectively and efficiently.
- Ensure seamless integration and data consistency between internal systems and the graph database.
- Work with the engineering team to deploy models into production, ensuring they operate at scale and with high reliability.
- Develop and implement monitoring tools and alerts for production models.
- Continuously evaluate and iterate on models based on performance metrics and feedback from users and stakeholders.
- Analyze data to extract insights and build data visualizations to support business intelligence and decision-making.
- Utilize data visualization libraries and BI tools to create dashboards and reports for various stakeholders.
- Collaborate with UX/UI teams to ensure machine learning features enhance user experience.
- Stay updated with the latest trends and advancements in AI and machine learning to bring innovation and improvements to our solutions.
- Work in short sprints on a POC/MVP basis and iterate models over time.

Qualifications/Skills:
- Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Data Science, or a related technical field.
- Proven experience in machine learning, data science, or a similar role.
- Strong proficiency in programming languages such as Python and frameworks/libraries like TensorFlow, PyTorch, and Scikit-Learn.
- Experience with graph databases, particularly TigerGraph, or a willingness to learn and adapt to it quickly.
- Experience with cloud platforms (AWS, Google Cloud, Azure) and understanding of deploying applications at scale.
- Experience in integrating and ensuring data consistency between multiple systems.
- Experience working with UX/UI teams to implement machine learning features that enhance user experience.
- Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy.
- Proven experience in developing monitoring tools and setting up alerts for production models.
- Ability to analyze complex data sets and provide actionable insights through data visualizations.
- Strong skills in data visualization tools and techniques, with experience using BI tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or Looker to create dashboards and visual reports.
- Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to work in a fast-paced, startup environment.
- Extensive math and computer skills, with a deep understanding of probability, statistics, and algorithms.
- Familiarity with data structures, data modeling, and software architecture.
- Effective communication skills, both written and verbal, to collaborate with cross-functional teams.

item.title: Seeking a Power BI expert to construct a dashboard linked to two live data sources. - Upwork
item.description:
We are in search of a specialist skilled in Microsoft Power BI to create a dashboard that will report on our client's IT helpdesk metrics. We need an expert who can advise us on the best practices for establishing Power BI dashboards.

Project Overview:

The dashboard should consist of one or two pages and must be exportable to PDF for inclusion in larger monthly reports. It will draw data from two sources:

Syncro RMM - https://community.syncromsp.com/t/power-bi/12173 & https://community.syncromsp.com/t/database-exports/12175
HaloPSA - https://halopsa.com/integrations/power-bi-psa-integration/

Ideally the data displayed is no more than 24 hrs old, even better if it's live data.

The dashboard should include the following metrics, displayed as gauges or tiles that can be moved around to suit different layouts:

Asset & Device Metrics:
Total device counts of PCs, servers, and other network devices.
Breakdown of workstations by their age.
Percentage of workstations covered by warranty and not.
Percentage of devices with antivirus installed.
Percentage of devices that are fully patched.
A list of firewalls with model numbers and operating system versions.
Total number of alerts detected and total number resolved in the last 12 months.
Total number of alerts detected and total number resolved in the last 30 days months.

Support and Ticket Metrics:
Total number of new tickets lodged and total number tickets resolved in last 12 months.
Total number of new tickets lodged and total number tickets resolved in last 30 days.
Average customer satisfaction last 12 months.
A pie chart of ticket categories logged in the last 30 days and 12 months.

Other Requirements:

- The connection of data must be secure.
- The dashboard must be easily filterable by client name.
- Ideally, we can drill down into data formatted as a list when clicking on one of the above "tiles".
- We need the ability to change date ranges for the above metrics on the fly as required.
- The dashboard should be designed so that it can be built upon and improved in future iterations and the data queries should be readable by other people.
- Use our company colour scheme and logo where it makes sense.
- We rely on your expertise to tell us what is required to make this work, but we are more than capable of procuring the required licenses, setting up the API access, etc. to ensure you have everything you need to create the data source connections and build the dashboard.

If this project is successful, we will have additional work and more dashboards for you to develop.

Hourly Range: $22.00-$54.00

Category: Data Visualization
Skills:API Integration, Microsoft Power BI, Data Visualization, Data Analysis
Skills: API Integration, Microsoft Power BI, Data Visualization, Data Analysis
